contact_name: Publications Office of the European Union
description: The Interinstitutional procedures name authority list (NAL) or Common Authority Table (CAT) is a controlled vocabulary listing the procedures that are part of the legal decision making process with their authority code and label(s) in the 24 official languages of the EU (when available). The Interinstitutional procedures NAL is part of the Core Metadata (CM) used in the exchange between the institutions involved in the legal decision making process and the Publications Office of the EU. The NAL is under governance of the Interinstitutional Metadata Maintenance Committee (IMMC) and maintained  by the Publications Office of the EU in its Metadata Registry (MDR)
title: Interinstitutional procedures Name Authority List
name: procedure
